g.title: **Invariant**: - Blocked in `epoll_wait()` - Kernel Ready List is empty - CPU in C-state (Power Save)
**Invariant**: - Inside `while(1)` or `for(;;)` - `listen_fd` is `O_NONBLOCK` - Draining kernel backlog
**CRITICAL BUG**: - Handshake complete - `listen_fd` remains in kernel queue - No new ET trigger possible

ul.li: Kernel: Moves listen_fd to ready list once.
Requirement: Application must call accept() until EAGAIN.
Failure: If only 1 is accepted, 49 remain in the accept() queue.
Result: epoll_wait will not wake up again for these 49 because no new edge transition (Empty -> Data) occurs until the 51st client arrives.
